Jigawa State Hisbah Command says it has deployed 1223 of its personnel to impose a ban on Dj dance, Gala and other social vices, especially during the Eid-El-Fitr celebration. State Commandant, Malam Ibrahim Dahiru stated this in a statement issued to newsmen in Dutse the state capital. He said the personnel were deployed to mosques and other public places where the Sallah celebration is taking place across the state for the maintenance of law and order. Dahiru added that the command has also banned the sale and use of firecrackers during the period. He noted that during the period Hisba guards would stage a patrol to ensure it arrested those who engaged in immoral activities. The state Commandant, therefore, advised parents to monitor the movements of their wards, especially during the Sallah festivities.